## Gap 3 — Δ_KG Exclusion from Base Paper Cost is Unjustified

### What the gap is
The base paper cost is taken as 7.3728 ms = Δ_Enc (1.5298 ms) + Δ_Dec (5.8430 ms). The Key Generation step Δ_KG (0.8549 ms) is excluded because Algorithm 5 (QC-LDPC KeyGen) runs once per data-sharing session, not per packet. However, this exclusion was not justified in the original paper text. Under strict single-use ssk interpretation, Δ_KG could be counted per packet → base = 8.2277 ms → reduction = 99.1%.

### Why it matters to a reviewer
> *"Why did you exclude Δ_KG from the base paper per-packet cost? If you are comparing per-packet costs and ssk is single-use, then KG runs per packet. Your baseline is cherry-picked to be lower."*

### Fix Type
**Claim fix** (paper) + **Code documentation**

### Fix Location 1 — Paper
**File:** [C:\Users\aloob\Downloads\Research Backup\simulation\results\novelty_proof_and_results.md](file:///Users/aloob/Downloads/Research%20Backup/simulation/results/novelty_proof_and_results.md)
**Section:** §4.1 — Gap 3 blockquote

**What was written:**
```
> [GAP 3 — BEST FIX: Conservative value as strength signal]
> Base paper per-packet HE cost is taken as 7.3728 ms (Δ_Enc + Δ_Dec only).
> Δ_KG (0.8549 ms) is excluded on the basis that QC-LDPC Key Generation
> (Algorithm 5) is performed once per data-sharing session — not per packet —
> consistent with Algorithm 5's invocation pattern and the proposed model's
> Phase 1.2 treatment.
> Note: if Δ_KG is counted per packet under strict single-use ssk interpretation,
> the base cost becomes 8.2277 ms and the reduction becomes 99.1% — a stronger
> claim. The conservative 7.3728 ms is used throughout, making the 97.3%–99.0%
> range a lower bound.
```

### Fix Location 2 — Simulation Code
**File:** [C:\Users\aloob\Downloads\Research Backup\simulation\sim_latency.m](file:///Users/aloob/Downloads/Research%20Backup/simulation/sim_latency.m)
