## Gap 4 — Break-Even at N=4 Hides the N<4 Disadvantage

### What the gap is
The proposed scheme is slower than the base paper for N=1, N=2, N=3 packets per epoch because the epoch initiation cost (22.55 ms) dominates. The original presentation only mentioned "break-even at N=4" without showing what happens before break-even. A reviewer aware of short-session IoT scenarios could challenge this.

### Why it matters to a reviewer
