> The range is a lower-bounded claim, not an upper-bounded one.
```

**Also updated:** Summary Table row reads `24×–33× reduction (worst-case anchored)`. Conclusion item 3 updated.

### How it favours novelty
The **key defensive strength**: at the worst-case floor of 24×, the proposed scheme is still lower than every competitor (Lizard: 5.50, RLizard: 8.05, LEDAkem: 2.85). No realistic cycle estimate can reverse this ordering. The range 24×–33× is presented as a lower-bounded claim — the floor is already the best figure in the comparison table. This makes the metric immune to measurement methodology objections.

